-- Italy’s Gasoline Demand Slumps 16% in April, Ministry Data Show
-- B y   L a n a n h   N g u y e n
-- 2012-05-15T13:09:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-15/italy-s-gasoline-demand-slumps-16-in-april-ministry-data-show.html
Italy’s gasoline consumption dropped
16.1 percent in April to 675,000 metric tons from 805,000 tons a
year earlier, according to data from the  Ministry of Economic
Development .  Diesel demand fell to 1.86 million tons last month, down
14.3 percent from the previous year, the data showed.  The country’s total fuel demand declined 14.1 percent in
April to 5.12 million tons from 5.96 million tons in the same
month a year earlier.  To contact the reporter on this story:
